\ lifted from park 
map{ roomgen{ 
0 value panchorx 
0 value panchory 
0 value buildauto_spriteoff
0 value sizex
0 value sizey 
0 value doorx 
0 value doory 
0 value loc_name 
0 value awk_anch_x
0 value awk_anch_y
0 value awk_size_x
0 value awk_size_y 

\ ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
\ ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

\ As of 17-01-26, this tool is experimental and still being developed. It is operational though. 

\ ** MODDER TOOL : PREFAB GENERATOR ** 
\ Prefabs are hardcoded so this thingie makes them for you. High fidelity buildings! 

\ You can use a different spritesheet if you want, i use the misc buildings one. 
\ in this case you will need to adjust some things below and in the arguments.

\ For best results, DONT align your building's floor sprite with a multiple of 16 (i.e a tile) 

\ There is secondary part to this - see the below mapping and calling of sycamore_prefab_generator for further setup 
\ Eventually I will copy this file for forge.df, which is a new rare loc for TRACHEA. 

\ DEVLOG: 
\ 21-01-25 - deprecated old object anchor method, added doorx, doory, location string, awkward_shape arguments, added alt func with prefab core 
\ 23-01-25 - spoke with Madgarden, who said he'd look into improving things for TRACHEA - namely, more script-exposed tile variables. 


: sycamore_prefab_generator ( walkspace_size_x , walkspace_size_y , walkstart_x , walkstart_y , location_string, doorx , doory , sprite offset , sizex , sizey ) 
	to sizey \ building x size in tiles 
	to sizex \ building y size in tiles 
	to buildauto_spriteoff \ spriteid of first tile, measured from top left 
	to doory \ y tile position of door on sprite, considering that first tile is (1,1) 
	to doorx \ x tile position of door, considering that first tile is (1,1) 
	to loc_name \ name of location, *MUST BE A STRING* 
	
	\ "awkward shape" args, for wonky buildings. 
	\ set all args of this to 0 if you have a nice rectangular building or dont need it 
	to awk_anch_y \ y tile position of walkspace on sprite, considering that first tile is (1,1)  
	to awk_anch_x \ x tile position of walkspace on sprite, considering that first tile is (1,1) 
	to awk_size_y \ y size of walkspace in tiles
	to awk_size_x \ x size of walkspace in tiles 
	\ Anchor tile will also be walkable. 

	xyp.xy tile>pos to panchory to panchorx
	
	sizey for \ y , j 
		sizex for \ x , i 
		
		\ debug stuff commented out 
		
			\ "I AND J" print 
			\ i 16 * j 16 * pos>tile .. print
			\ "SUPERPOSITION" print 
			\ panchorx panchory i 16 * j 16 * xyadd pos>tile .. print
			
			panchorx panchory i 16 * j 16 * xyadd pos>tile tile@ dup LAYER_WALLSIDE buildauto_spriteoff i 1 - + j 1 - 14 * + .lspriteid! 
			\ You will need to change the 14 for other spritesheets, coz in the misc buildings one there are 14 sprites per line.
		
			panchorx panchory i 16 * j 16 * xyadd pos>tile tile@ TILE_BLOCK swap .id! 
		
		\ Here I construct the door. 
		\ As measured from the top-left building tile origin, which is considered (1,1) 
		\ "Why arent my rooms generating?" the game doesnt like you using ndx, nad, and filter-only here. 
		\ You will also need to setup a location in the traditional way. 
			i doorx = j doory = and if \ was 2,6 
				panchorx panchory i 16 * j 16 * xyadd pos>tile tile@ TILE_LINK_DOOR swap .id!
				panchorx panchory i 16 * j 16 * xyadd pos>tile tile@ loc_name $picklocid addloc swap .locationid!
				
				
				\ setting roomid always crashes 
		
			then 
			\ ndx = no door exit (room will not be first room)
			\ nad = no auto door (no random doors to random rooms) 
		
		next drop 
	next drop 
	
	\ awkward shape logic 
	\ only enabled when params are nonzero 
	
	awk_size_y for \ y , j 
		awk_size_x for \ x , i 
	
			awk_size_x 0 > awk_size_y 0 > and if 
				panchorx panchory i 16 * j 16 * xyadd pos>tile awk_anch_x 1 - awk_anch_y 1 - xyadd tile@ TILE_FLOOR swap .id! 
					\ can choose a different id if you want - TILE_BLOCK_FLOOR allows bullets but not players for example
					
					\ " YOU CAN WALK AT " print 
					\ panchorx panchory i 16 * j 16 * xyadd pos>tile awk_anch_x 1 - awk_anch_y 1 - xyadd " , " swap .. .. print 
			then 
		
		next drop
	next drop
	
; 

\ ** USAGE EXAMPLE : ** 
\ 3 3 5 1 "armory" 2 6 building_misc_tiles_base_id 126 + 7 6 sycamore_prefab_generator
\ to generate to generate a 7x6 building with the door at (2,6) , with "armory" as the loc , with 3x3 walkable space starting nat (5,1) 


\ ** Below is an extremely similar generator, except it uses the hardcoded prefab words

\ ++ more consistent roomgen behaviour 
\ -- imposes minimum size 

: sycamore_prefab_generator_alt ( walkspace_size_x , walkspace_size_y , walkstart_x , walkstart_y , location_string, doorx , doory , sprite offset , sizex , sizey ) 
	to sizey \ building x size in tiles 
	to sizex \ building y size in tiles 
	to buildauto_spriteoff \ spriteid of first tile, measured from top left 
	to doory \ y tile position of door on sprite, considering that first tile is (1,1) 
	to doorx \ x tile position of door, considering that first tile is (1,1) 
	to loc_name \ name of location, *MUST BE A STRING* 
	
	\ "awkward shape" args, for wonky buildings. 
	\ set all args of this to 0 if you have a nice rectangular building or dont need it 
	to awk_anch_y \ y tile position of walkspace on sprite, considering that first tile is (1,1)  
	to awk_anch_x \ x tile position of walkspace on sprite, considering that first tile is (1,1) 
	to awk_size_y \ y size of walkspace in tiles
	to awk_size_x \ x size of walkspace in tiles 
	\ Anchor tile will also be walkable. 

	xyp.xy tile>pos to panchory to panchorx
	
		\ generates a 3x2 (3x3?) prefab then just overwrites it
		\ obviously, if your building isnt big enough, you are about to have an issue. 
			panchorx panchory pos>tile doorx doory xyadd -1 1 xyadd tanchor!
			loc_name $picklocid addloc 
			prefab{
			0 3 1 shop }
	
	sizey for \ y , j 
		sizex for \ x , i 
			
			panchorx panchory i 16 * j 16 * xyadd pos>tile tile@ dup LAYER_WALLTOP buildauto_spriteoff i 1 - + j 1 - 14 * + .lspriteid! 
			\ You will need to change the 14 for other spritesheets, coz in the misc buildings one there are 14 sprites per line.
		
			panchorx panchory i 16 * j 16 * xyadd pos>tile tile@ .id@ TILE_LINK_DOOR = not if 
				panchorx panchory i 16 * j 16 * xyadd pos>tile tile@ TILE_BLOCK swap .id! 
			then 
		
		next drop 
	next drop 
	
	panchorx panchory pos>tile doorx doory xyadd tile@ dup LAYER_WALLSIDE 0 .lspriteid! 
	\ undo the prefab door tile sprite - i am assuming you have your own! 
	
	\ awkward shape logic 
	\ only enabled when params are nonzero 
	
	awk_size_y for \ y , j 
		awk_size_x for \ x , i 
	
			awk_size_x 0 > awk_size_y 0 > and if 
				panchorx panchory i 16 * j 16 * xyadd pos>tile awk_anch_x 1 - awk_anch_y 1 - xyadd tile@ TILE_FLOOR swap .id! 
					\ see regular non-alt func for comments here
			then 
		
		next drop
	next drop
	
; 




: diningset
	table
	75 %chance if chair -1 movey drift then
	75 %chance if chair 1 movey drift then
	50 %chance if chair -1 movex drift then
	50 %chance if chair 1 movex drift then
;


} }
	
0 value gbx
0 value gby
0 value gbx2
0 value gby2

' plotgrass >defer ft

: pt
	xyp.xy ft // Plot the current floor by default
	
	xyp.i char P = if xyp.xy 3 2 5 1 "madgardhouse" 2 6 building_misc_tiles_base_id 126 + 7 6 sycamore_prefab_generator_alt xyp.xy sycatilegrassset then;
	xyp.i char F = if xyp.xy 0 0 0 0 "armorytest" 2 6 building_misc_tiles_base_id 126 7 + + 4 6 sycamore_prefab_generator_alt xyp.xy sycatilegrassset then;
	
	xyp.i char X = if xyp.xy roadsign1 lt-here then;
	xyp.i char H = if xyp.xy roadsign2 lt-here then;
	xyp.i char C = if xyp.xy streetlamp lt-here lt .pos 8 8 xyadd lt .pos! then;
	 
	 xyp.i char t = if xyp.xy tree_exclusive lt-here -0.5 0.5 frnd dup lt .vel! xyp.xy sycatilegrassset  then;
	 xyp.i char G = if xyp.xy parkbushes lt-here xyp.xy sycatilegrassset  then;

	 xyp.i char [ = if xyp.xy sycatilegrassedge_vert then;
	
	 xyp.i char 8 = if xyp.xy sycatilegrassset then;	 
	 xyp.i char W = if walktile xyp.xy sycatilegrassset then;	
	 
	xyp.i char a = if fencea xyp.xy sycatilegrassset then;
	xyp.i char A = if fenceA xyp.xy sycatilegrassset then;
	xyp.i char b = if fenceb xyp.xy sycatilegrassset then;
	xyp.i char B = if fenceB xyp.xy sycatilegrassset then;

;

